I got the guacamole greens and loved it (be careful though how much dressing you ask for--it's good but a little strong). That being said, it's not somewhere I would go frequently as the prices are a little high for a salad (though understandably given the ingredient quality) and they don't have enough variety-- and their make your own salad bowls get pretty steep as each topping is $1-5 after paying $6.50 for the base. Still a good place for an occasional healthy meal though.
